dcterms:description: A dataset constructed from the complete 2015 English-language Wikipedia dump, composed of seven different topical types, each containing at least five sub-topical categories. On average, each sub-topical category contains a list of 20 items or concepts.
dcterms:title: 2015 English-language Wikipedia dump

dcterms:description: A collection of seven annotated datasets that differ in terms of topical content and complexity, used to evaluate the EVE model's performance in various tasks.
dcterms:title: Seven annotated datasets

dcterms:creator: T. Mikolov
K. Chen
G. Corrado
J. Dean
dcterms:description: A word embedding model that efficiently estimates word representations in vector space, widely used in various natural language processing tasks.
dcterms:title: Word2Vec

dcterms:description: A word embedding model that represents words as vectors and incorporates subword information, improving the quality of word representations.
dcterms:title: FastText

dcterms:creator: J. Pennington
R. Socher
C. D. Manning
dcterms:description: A word embedding model that provides global vectors for word representation, leveraging global statistical information from a corpus.
dcterms:title: GloVe

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of Wikipedia categories and articles used in the EVE model to generate word embeddings.
dcterms:title: Wikipedia categories and articles (used in EVE model)
